Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #medium saucepan{} (with a tight-fitting #lid{}) on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Stir in the @korma style paste{50%g} and half the garlic, then cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Stir the @basmati rice{150%g}, @vegetable stock paste{10} and @water for the rice{300%ml}(cold) into the onion pan and bring to the boil.

Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

While the rice cooks, trim the @green beans{80%g} and cut into thirds. Trim and coarsely grate the @carrot{1}(coarsely grated) (no need to peel). Zest and halve the @lime{½}.

Finely chop the @coriander{1}(finely chopped, stalks and all), then pop into a #small bowl{} with a squeeze of lime juice and the @olive oil for the dressing{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then mix together.

Taste and add more salt, pepper and lime juice if needed, then set your coriander dressing aside.

When the rice has 10 mins left, heat a drizzle of oil in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the green beans and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir-fry until starting to char, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Once charred, add the @king prawns{300%g} to the beans and stir-fry for ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in the remaining garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more, then remove from the heat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw prawns. The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Once the rice is cooked, fluff it up with a #fork{} and stir through the grated carrot. Add the rice and lime zest to the prawn pan and stir together until combined. Taste and add salt and pepper if needed.

Spoon the prawn pilaf into bowls, then drizzle with the coriander dressing and add a dollop of @low fat natural yoghurt{75%g}.

Cut the remaining @lime{remaining}(cut into wedges) into wedges and serve alongside for squeezing over.

Enjoy!